	(74,1,'2014-02-10 06:10:27','2014-02-10 06:10:27','<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Make it worth it. - Rachelle S.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I was introduced to web development by myÂ <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">boyfriend</a> last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. then i wanna know more. and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. The only break i have was sleep. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">AndÂ  since I can see that it has many opportunities and i enjoy it as much as designing I decided that I am going to do this not as a hobby but i will learn this deeply. And so, with 3 years in advertising background in college, I decided that I want to be a front end web developer, as I know its where I am more capable of.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n&nbsp;','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-02-10 06:10:27','2014-02-10 06:10:27','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=74',0,'revision','',0),
	(75,1,'2014-02-10 06:21:01','2014-02-10 06:21:01','<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Make it worth it. - Rachelle S.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I was introduced to web development by myÂ <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">boyfriend</a> last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners such as myself) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. Then I just wanna know more and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. The only break i have was sleep. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">AndÂ  since I can see that it has many opportunities and i enjoy it as much as i enjoy designing ads I decided that I am going to do this not as a hobby but i will learn this deeper. And so, with 3 years in advertising background in college, I decided that I want to be a front end web developer, as I know its where I am more capable of.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I will make time learning about web development worth it. By hard work and never giving up spirit, I am hoping to get good and apply the skills i am acquiring in my future projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Watch out! ;)</p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-02-10 06:21:01','2014-02-10 06:21:01','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=75',0,'revision','',0),
	(76,1,'2014-02-10 06:22:07','2014-02-10 06:22:07','<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Make it worth it. - Rachelle S.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I was introduced to web development by myÂ <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">boyfriend</a> last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners such as myself) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. Then I just wanna know more and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">AndÂ  since I can see that it has many opportunities and i enjoy it as much as i enjoy designing ads I decided that I am going to do this not as a hobby but i will learn this deeper. And so, with 3 years in advertising background in college, I decided that I want to be a front end web developer, as I know its where I am more capable of.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I will make time learning about web development worth it. By hard work and never giving up spirit, I am hoping to get good and apply the skills i am acquiring in my future projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Watch out! ;)</p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-02-10 06:22:07','2014-02-10 06:22:07','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=76',0,'revision','',0),
	(77,1,'2014-02-10 06:28:11','2014-02-10 06:28:11','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I was introduced to web development by myÂ <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">boyfriend</a> last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners such as myself) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. Then I just wanna know more and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I can see that it has many opportunities and i enjoy it as much as i enjoy designing ads so I decided that I am going to learn this deeper. And with 3 yearsÂ  advertising background in college, I decided that I am going to be a front end web developer, as where i want to excel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I will make time learning about web development worth it. By hard work, natural talent and never giving up spirit, I am hoping to get good and apply the skills i am acquiring in my future projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Watch out! ;)</p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-02-10 06:28:11','2014-02-10 06:28:11','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=77',0,'revision','',0),
	(78,1,'2014-05-19 07:23:24','2014-05-19 07:23:24','<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Make it worth it. -Rachelle S.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I was introduced to web development by my <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">partner</a>Â  last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners such as myself) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. Then I just wanna know more and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I can see that it has many opportunities and I enjoy it as much as I enjoy designing ads so I decided that I am going to learn this deeper. And with 3 yearsÂ  advertising background in college, I decided that I need to be a front end web developer, as where I want to excel.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I am making my time, energy and efforts worth it. I will let hard work, natural talent and never giving up spirit take care of my portfolio. I\'m really hoping to get good and apply the skills I am acquiring to my future projects.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">My name is<strong> Rachelle Ann Salvadora</strong>. So what is <strong>manak</strong> all about? I call Giolliano manok. So, as the female version of him he called me manak. And since it sounds unique I am making it my trademark.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Also I\'m going to be posting about my experiences outside programming/development. I\'m just gonna be sharing stuff here and there about random things or thi.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Watch out!</p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-19 07:23:24','2014-05-19 07:23:24','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=78',0,'revision','',0),
	(79,1,'2014-02-10 06:32:40','2014-02-10 06:32:40','<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Make it worth it. -Rachelle</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I was introduced to web development by myÂ <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">boyfriend</a> last October 2013, I haven\'t really thought of seriously getting into it by that time. I was just enjoying how amazing it is (for beginners such as myself) to make a web page. For a complete noob like me it feels great to finish one. Then I just wanna know more and before i know it i was addicted to it. I do not want to sleep at all. Sadly I had to stop because I have other responsibilities and i have not consider web development as a career.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I can see that it has many opportunities and i enjoy it as much as i enjoy designing ads so I decided that I am going to learn this deeper. And with 3 yearsÂ  advertising background in college, I decided that I am going to be a front end web developer, as where i want to excel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I am making my time, energy and efforts worth it. I will let hard work, natural talent and never giving up spirit take care of my portfolio. I\'m really hoping to get good and apply the skills i am acquiring in my future projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Watch out! ;)</p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-02-10 06:32:40','2014-02-10 06:32:40','',2,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=79',0,'revision','',0),
