	(91,1,'2014-02-14 11:02:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I always see an article about women and programming, women and technology, or something about women and computer and how the world should attract women to code but I never knew/heard/read that the first considered programmer is a woman. Yes, men. A woman who is also a mother of three.\r\n\r\nLady Ada Lovelace.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rachellesalvadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ada.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-109\" alt=\"ada\" src=\"http://rachellesalvadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ada.jpg\" width=\"402\" height=\"402\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI remember reading an article about giving women someone to look up to in tech industry, guess what? They never mention the mother of programming. I was shocked when i first heard of her because I\'ve never seen an article that aims to inspire women to code mentioned her. Personally, I thought that the first programmer was a male. I don\'t know if it is true but it seems that not most programmers know about her. (or I don\'t know if its just me because you know,Â  I\'m still at the very beginning stage)\r\n\r\nIf programmers or their community really want to inspire women to code as they are claiming,Â  they need Ada Lovelace. It\'s not that we (women) will try to be a math genius as she was or what, but it is always a good feeling that if she did it, we can as well. And this can be a positive attitude for women to actually try. Plus, it seems like she is fashionable, elegant and still manages to live like a woman should and would want.\r\n\r\nProgramming always has this image in us that people or girls who only do it are boring, dull and anti-socials. Look! She seems beautiful, elegant and graceful.\r\n\r\nIts an issue today that women are leaving the tech world. Why? Because there is a feeling that we don\'t belong. Before I learn the first language that I use today, coding was like a language that alien speaks. Surely not English like in the movies. The reason why there are less and less women in this field is because I though it is obvious that it is a guy thing.\r\n\r\nBut when i discovered Lady Ada, I\'m literally confused.It gives me a little bit of confidence that I can learn and understand how to program, like a pro (Okay. Maybe not like a pro but still can program) .\r\n\r\nSeriously, she could be what we(girls) need to know about and not this popular information that girls are actually abandoning the tech community because to be honest, its pressuring to know that there is only going to be 2-3 girls in the area where you work and that you guys expect more from you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-02-14 11:02:17','2014-02-14 11:02:17','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=91',0,'post','',0),
	(92,1,'2014-02-13 03:25:08','2014-02-13 03:25:08','I always see an article about women and programming, women and technology, or something about coding and women and how the world should attract women to code but I never knew that the first considered programmer is a woman. Yes, men. A Woman/female/girl who is also a mother of three.\r\n\r\nI present to you, Lady Ada Lovelace.\r\n\r\n<img id=\"irc_mi\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.primermagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/AdaLovelace/AdaLovelace_Feature.jpg\" width=\"530\" height=\"260\" />\r\n\r\nI remember reading an article about giving women someone to look up top in the tech industry, guess what? They never mention the mother of programming. I was shocked when i first heard of her because I\'ve never seen an article that aims to inspire women to code mentioned her. I don\'t know if it is true but it seems that not most programmers know about her. (or I don\'t know if its just me because you know, I\'m still at the beginning stage)\r\n\r\nIf programmers or their community really want to inspire women to code as they are claiming, Lady Ada Lovelace needs to be exposed. It\'s not that we (women) will try to be a math genius or what, but it is always a good feeling that if she did it, we can as well. And this can be a positive attitude for women to actually try. Plus, it seems like she is fashionable, elegant and still manages to live like a woman should and would want.\r\n\r\nProgramming always has this image in us that people or girls who only do it are boring,\r\n\r\nIts an issue today that women are leaving the tech world. Before I learn the first language that I use today, coding was like a language that alien speaks for me. Surely not English like in movies. The reason why there are less and less women in this field is because I though it is obvious that it is a guy thing.\r\n\r\nBut when i discovered Lady Ada, I\'m literally confused. Suddenly i felt little bit of of confidence that I can learn and understand how to program, like a pro (Okay. Maybe not like a pro but still can program) .\r\n\r\nSeriously, she could be what we(girls) need to know about and not this popular information that girls are actually abandoning the tech community because to be honest, its pressuring to know that there is only going to be 2-3 girls in the area where you work and that you guys expect girls in this industry to do so much better just because we are trying to fit in \"your\" environment.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','','','inherit','open','open','','91-revision-v1','','','2014-02-13 03:25:08','2014-02-13 03:25:08','',91,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=92',0,'revision','',0),
	(93,1,'2014-02-13 05:19:10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Last Friday,Â  February 7, 2014.Â  My niece, who is in kinder garden went to me after his school and gave me his notebook, as his parents are both not available. On his notebook the teacher wrote:\n\n(Exactly as written. With all the capitalization, format, and the use of \"s\".\n\n&nbsp;','Philippine education system','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-02-13 05:19:10','2014-02-13 05:19:10','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=93',0,'post','',0),
	(94,1,'2014-02-13 05:22:29','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Its funny how we claim that we (Filipinos) are catching up with the modern technology and think that we are up-to-date.\r\n\r\nI am just starting to learn how to code and all my sources are up-to-date and on international basis. Thanks to my <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">partner/teacher</a>. I didn\'t really cared about how the technology in the Philippines is doing because the media seems to make it seem like we are following the trend based on international standards plus my goal is to work overseas to be with my better half.\r\n\r\nIts just recently that I wondered how the web development in the Philippines is catching up because in some countries, they are already arguing about if it is necessary for the kids to learn how to code. Plus I\'m hoping to get involved in the conferences and events to learn deeper.Â  So, I searched for the organizations, groups and corporations that deals with web development in the Philippines. My curiosity landed me to a list of the websites that deals with these kind of stuff in my motherland.\r\n\r\nResult? I stopped halfway, depressed of what I discovered.Â  Our technology is hundred years behind other countries.Â  The Philippine Web: communities, groups, organizations &amp; conferences. My reaction? A sad face and a broken heart. :(\r\n\r\nLook at them yourself and you will be broken hearted too.\r\n<blockquote>This is the list of <strong>Web Related</strong> Communities, Groups, Organizations &amp; Conferences in the Philippines for Web Designers, Web Users, Web Developers, Bloggers, Internet Marketers &amp; Enthusiasts\r\n\r\nHope that list is good for you.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.e-commercephilippines.com/\">Digital Filipino Club</a></strong> â€“ is the Philippines premiere e-commerce community composed of business minded-enthusiasts, entrepreneurs, and professionals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://blogwatch.ph/\">BlogWatch</a></strong> â€“ The group aims to tap the burgeoning blogosphere in the Philippines to provide different perspectives on the elections apart from that of traditional media.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.piusonline.com\">Philippine Internet Users Society</a></strong> â€“ a nonprofit organization and a movement of all Filipino Internet users dedicated to serving the interests of the growing community of Internet users in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://forums.seo.ph\">SEO Philippines</a></strong> â€“ the largest and most active Internet marketing organization in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.philweavers.net/forums/\">PhilWeavers</a></strong> â€“ The Philippine Webdesignersâ€™ Network is an online global network of Filipino Web Designers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.pwag.org/aboutpwag.htm\">Philippine Web Accessibility Group</a></strong> â€“ A Philippine Initiative to UN Web Accessibility Design Compliance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.phpugph.com/\">PHP User Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ (PHPUGPH) A non-profit organization established to provide support for LAMP (Linux, Apache MySQL, PHP) and open-source enthusiasts in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://webdesigners.org.ph\">Philippine Web Designers Organization</a></strong> â€“ a group of professionals and hobbyists who create human interfaces for the Web, champion the use of standards, accessibility &amp; usability, and aim to uplift the state of web design in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://iblogph.org/\">iBlog: Philippine Blogging Summit</a></strong> â€“ is one of the top internet marketing and blogging conferences in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.devcon.ph\">DEVCON</a></strong> â€“ events are gatherings designed to facilitate interaction among the software and web development professionals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://philippines.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp Philippines</a></strong> â€“ conference that focuses on everything WordPress.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.facebookgarage.ph/\">Facebook Developer Garage Philippines</a></strong> â€“ an open conferences, participatory workshop-events for everyone who want to explore more about Facebook Platform, Social Media Marketing and monetize from Facebook Platform!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://sites.google.com/site/gtugph/\">Google Technology Users Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ is an independent user group with interest in Google technologies and is entirely independent from Google Inc., the corporation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://forum.joomla.org/viewforum.php?f=242\">Joomla! User Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ The community of Pinoy Joomla!, ka-Joomla! &amp; Filipino Joomla user!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.mozillaphilippines.org\">Mozilla Philippines Community</a></strong> â€“ Firefox and Mozilla technologies in the Philippines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://groups.drupal.org/philippines\">Philippines Drupal Users Group</a></strong> â€“ Community of Filipino Drupal users in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://blog.proudcloud.net/\">Roofcamp</a></strong> â€“ is a venue for Technopreneurs, influencers, innovators, coders, designers, artists, VCs &amp; Angels, philanthropists, <a title=\"Startups\" href=\"http://webgeek.ph/category/startups/\" rel=\"nofollow\">startups</a>, and other like minded individuals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.pinoywebstartup.com/\">Pinoy Web Startup</a></strong> â€“ profiles and tracks web products and services, highlighting those produced by Philippine and/or Asian web companies in the early stages.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://pinoyrb.org\">Philippine Ruby Users Group</a></strong> â€“ A <em>group</em> of <em>users</em> and/or programmers in the <em>Philippines</em> using the <em>Ruby</em> Programming Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://webgeek.ph/\"><strong>WebGeek Philippines</strong></a> â€“ is community that acts as a venue for Webmasters, Web Designers &amp; Web Developers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nsource:Â  <a href=\"http://webgeek.ph/the-philippine-web-communities-groups-organizations-conferences/\">http://webgeek.ph/the-philippine-web-communities-groups-organizations-conferences/</a></blockquote>\r\nIs it just me or this list was supposed to be a list of <strong>Web Related</strong> Communities, Groups, Organizations &amp; Conferences in the Philippines for Web Designers, Web Users, Web Developers, Bloggers, Internet Marketers &amp; Enthusiasts. I do not know if there is something wrong with my understanding here. As there was so many issues, I\'d like to make a separate blog on them soon because there is so many things going on and I have to focus on learning how to become a better web developer and take pride of my nationality. I don\'t mean to offend or anyone but I think somebody needs to point out what is wrong and I think we need to keep up.\r\n\r\nThere are web development related company websites that is still using flash. And the worst part? They still strongly require it from their applicants. I am about to email them and tell them that it is really not ideal nowadays to use flash but the email address is not using gmail. Seriously? I thought all web developers should be using gmail nowadays because it has way more better features than any other electronic mail service provider can do.\r\n\r\nI\'m sure we don\'t wanted to be addressed as a community who can\'t accept facts.\r\n\r\nI really want the Philippine web community to grow because we can get many opportunities from it. territorial\r\n\r\nThis is the list of <strong>Web Related</strong> Communities, Groups, Organizations &amp; Conferences in the Philippines for Web Designers, Web Users, Web Developers, Bloggers, Internet Marketers &amp; Enthusiasts\r\n\r\nHope that list is good for you.\r\n<span id=\"more-1096\"></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.e-commercephilippines.com/\">Digital Filipino Club</a></strong> â€“ is the Philippines premiere e-commerce community composed of business minded-enthusiasts, entrepreneurs, and professionals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://blogwatch.ph/\">BlogWatch</a></strong> â€“ The group aims to tap the burgeoning blogosphere in the Philippines to provide different perspectives on the elections apart from that of traditional media.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.piusonline.com\">Philippine Internet Users Society</a></strong> â€“ a nonprofit organization and a movement of all Filipino Internet users dedicated to serving the interests of the growing community of Internet users in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://forums.seo.ph\">SEO Philippines</a></strong> â€“ the largest and most active Internet marketing organization in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.philweavers.net/forums/\">PhilWeavers</a></strong> â€“ The Philippine Webdesignersâ€™ Network is an online global network of Filipino Web Designers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.pwag.org/aboutpwag.htm\">Philippine Web Accessibility Group</a></strong> â€“ A Philippine Initiative to UN Web Accessibility Design Compliance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.phpugph.com/\">PHP User Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ (PHPUGPH) A non-profit organization established to provide support for LAMP (Linux, Apache MySQL, PHP) and open-source enthusiasts in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://webdesigners.org.ph\">Philippine Web Designers Organization</a></strong> â€“ a group of professionals and hobbyists who create human interfaces for the Web, champion the use of standards, accessibility &amp; usability, and aim to uplift the state of web design in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://iblogph.org/\">iBlog: Philippine Blogging Summit</a></strong> â€“ is one of the top internet marketing and blogging conferences in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.devcon.ph\">DEVCON</a></strong> â€“ events are gatherings designed to facilitate interaction among the software and web development professionals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://philippines.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp Philippines</a></strong> â€“ conference that focuses on everything WordPress.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.facebookgarage.ph/\">Facebook Developer Garage Philippines</a></strong> â€“ an open conferences, participatory workshop-events for everyone who want to explore more about Facebook Platform, Social Media Marketing and monetize from Facebook Platform!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://sites.google.com/site/gtugph/\">Google Technology Users Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ is an independent user group with interest in Google technologies and is entirely independent from Google Inc., the corporation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://forum.joomla.org/viewforum.php?f=242\">Joomla! User Group Philippines</a></strong> â€“ The community of Pinoy Joomla!, ka-Joomla! &amp; Filipino Joomla user!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.mozillaphilippines.org\">Mozilla Philippines Community</a></strong> â€“ Firefox and Mozilla technologies in the Philippines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://groups.drupal.org/philippines\">Philippines Drupal Users Group</a></strong> â€“ Community of Filipino Drupal users in the Philippines.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://blog.proudcloud.net/\">Roofcamp</a></strong> â€“ is a venue for Technopreneurs, influencers, innovators, coders, designers, artists, VCs &amp; Angels, philanthropists, <a title=\"Startups\" href=\"http://webgeek.ph/category/startups/\" rel=\"nofollow\">startups</a>, and other like minded individuals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.pinoywebstartup.com/\">Pinoy Web Startup</a></strong> â€“ profiles and tracks web products and services, highlighting those produced by Philippine and/or Asian web companies in the early stages.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://pinoyrb.org\">Philippine Ruby Users Group</a></strong> â€“ A <em>group</em> of <em>users</em> and/or programmers in the <em>Philippines</em> using the <em>Ruby</em> Programming Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://webgeek.ph/\"><strong>WebGeek Philippines</strong></a> â€“ is community that acts as a venue for Webmasters, Web Designers &amp; Web Developers.</li>\r\n</ul>','Technology in the Philippines','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-02-13 05:22:29','2014-02-13 05:22:29','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=94',0,'post','',0),
	(95,1,'2014-02-13 05:22:29','2014-02-13 05:22:29','Its funny how we claim that we (Filipinos) are catching up with the modern technology and think that we are up-to-date.\r\n\r\nI am just starting to learn how to code and all my sources are up-to-date and on international basis. Thanks to my <a href=\"http://giolliano.com\">partner/teacher</a>. I didn\'t really cared about how the technology in the Philippines is doing because the media seems to make it seem like we are following the trend based on international standards plus my goal is to work overseas to be with my better half.\r\n\r\nIts just recently that I wondered how the web development in the Philippines is catching up because in some countries, they are already arguing about if it is necessary for the kids to learn how to code. Plus I\'m hoping to get involved in the conferences and events to learn deeper.Â  So, I searched for the organizations, groups and corporations that deals with web development in the Philippines. My curiosity landed me to a list of the websites that deals with these kind of stuff in my motherland.\r\n\r\nResult? I stopped halfway, depressed of what I discovered.Â  Our technology is hundred years behind other countries.Â  The Philippine Web: communities, groups, organizations &amp; conferences. My reaction? A sad face and a broken heart. :(\r\n\r\nLook at them yourself and you will be broken hearted too.\r\n<blockquote>This is the list of <strong>Web Related</strong> Communities, Groups, Organizations &amp; Conferences in the Philippines for Web Designers, Web Users, Web Developers, Bloggers, Internet Marketers &amp; Enthusiasts\r\n\r\nHope that list is good for you.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.e-commercephilippines.com/\">Digital Filipino Club</a></strong> â€“ is the Philippines premiere e-commerce community composed of business minded-enthusiasts, entrepreneurs, and professionals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://blogwatch.ph/\">BlogWatch</a><