	(97,1,'2014-02-13 12:33:46','2014-02-13 12:33:46','<strong>Introduction:</strong>\r\n\r\nWhat is PHP?\r\n\r\nPHP meant \"Personal Home Page\" when it was just beginning. Now itÂ  stands for \"Hypertext Processor\", a server-side scripting language that fits with HTML. This simply mean that HTML code can be inserted in a PHP file.\r\n\r\nWhy PHP?\r\n\r\nFor me, the very relative answer is to connect the design to the database.\r\n\r\n<strong>What you would need:</strong>\r\n\r\nServer or wampserver.\r\n\r\nText editor.\r\n\r\nBrowser.\r\n\r\nInternet.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAlso, most of the tutorials that i encountered was using Laravel. A fresh and handy framework for PHP. Sadly, I am using Windows7. Yes, I don\'t have the machine yet but it doesn\'t stop me from learning how to code.\r\n\r\nAlso, there are lots of tutorials on line for those who are really willing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Here are some helpful links:</strong>\r\n\r\nSee also:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/learn-php-fundamentals-from-scratch/#/\">Learn PHP Fundamentals From Scratch</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/getting-started-with-php-programming/#/\">PHP for Absolute Beginners</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/easy-phpeasy-2/#/\">Easy PHPeasy 2 - Objects, Frameworks &amp; Apps</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.codecademy.com/learn\">Learn to code while building a real project</a>\r\n\r\nSee also:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.homeandlearn.co.uk/php/php.html\">Beginners PHP</a>\r\n\r\nHere are some of the things that I learned. I will tackle them one at a time. I will make a list for now as It was pretty time consuming blogging about them while learning, plus, side projects, plus learning how to program in c.\r\n\r\nHere are the links of the codes and github. I\'ll update the article link when i managed to do one.\r\n\r\n<strong>Introduction to PHP</strong>\r\n-No github\r\n\r\n<strong>What is PHP</strong>\r\n-No github\r\n\r\n<strong>Setting up a server.</strong>\r\n-No github but will make an article on how to set up a server.\r\n\r\n<strong>First PHP file</strong>\r\n-github to be follow\r\n\r\n<strong>Echo/Print</strong>\r\n-github to be followed\r\n\r\n<strong>Variables</strong>\r\n-github to be followed\r\n\r\n<strong>Commenting code</strong>\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/4/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>If statement</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/5/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Switch statement\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/6/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Arithmetic operations</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/7/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Comparison operatiors</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/8/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Logical operators</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/9/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Triple equals</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/tree/1/10\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Switch statement</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/11/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Basic Arrays</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/12/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Arrays</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/tree/1/13\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Explode (String to array)</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/14/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Implode (Array to string)</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/15/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Outputting to a page</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/16/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Heredoc Syntax</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/blob/1/17/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\nThe github link for the PHP stuff that I learned. Most of them might seem senseless in a browser but it is actually about the code. I hope you can learn from them as well even if my purpose is just to compile and be able to explain them (I learn better this way). The articles that I will make are from a beginners point-of-view. In others words, from me. So it will relate to the ones who are just starting to learn PHP.\r\n\r\n<strong>PHP</strong>\r\n\r\n-<a href=\"https://github.com/rachellesalvadora/php/tree/1\" target=\"_blank\">github</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','All about PHP','','publish','open','open','','php','','','2014-02-13 21:12:26','2014-02-13 21:12:26','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=97',0,'post','',0),
