	(105,1,'2014-02-14 10:27:40','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Let me discuss the thing I usedÂ  to be able to learn PHP one by one as they are a requirement on every PHP related course that you will see on the internet.\r\n\r\n<strong>Server or wampserver.</strong>\r\n<blockquote>Â How to set up a server? This is how it is based on what i know.\r\n\r\nFirst get a good computer. A good computer which I don\'t have. It might seem funny to you that I\'m using a celeron in 2014 but I\'m not joking. For real. Ever article that I read require at least 4 GB RAM. Still funny, I have 2GB RAM. You can be confident that your machine will survive because I did.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>\r\n<strong>Text editor.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Browser.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Internet.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','What you need to Learn PHP','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-02-14 10:27:40','2014-02-14 10:27:40','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=105',0,'post','',0),
