	(202,1,'2014-07-11 06:05:10','2014-07-11 06:05:10','<strong>Step 1:</strong>\r\n\r\n-Read three design briefs\r\n\r\n-Apply one of the three design briefs to anything in your daily life.\r\n\r\n<strong>StepÂ </strong><strong>2:</strong>\r\n\r\nPick an activity; Make an interview &amp; observation plan\r\n\r\n1. Observations &amp; interviews through:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email</li>\r\n	<li>phone</li>\r\n	<li>skype</li>\r\n	<li>diary studies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n2. List types of people you might interview &amp; situations to come out w/ insights.\r\n\r\nDifferent types of users:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>everyday users</li>\r\n	<li>marginalized users</li>\r\n	<li>extreme users</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Step 3:</strong>\r\n\r\nChoose a design brief\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>what do you want to do w/ this info that you get</li>\r\n	<li>pick a \'main\' brief that your work address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Step 4:</strong>\r\n\r\nSelect 3 individuals &amp; observe\r\n\r\n- Select three people who are not similar to yourself to observe\r\n\r\n- Observe\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Successes</li>\r\n	<li>Breakdowns</li>\r\n	<li>Latent opportunities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\noccured when\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>used</li>\r\n	<li>not used</li>\r\n	<li>could be used</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNot need to be:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>representative of the \"general public\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Step 5:</strong>\r\n\r\nObserve and interview\r\n\r\n- tell the participants to perform the task as realistically as possibility\r\n\r\n- Take valid notes Â use digital photographs sketches to documents activities\r\n\r\n- Dont use video camera\r\n\r\n- Get only whats important\r\n\r\nAnswer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>when</li>\r\n	<li>where</li>\r\n	<li>how</li>\r\n</ul>\r\ncaption each photo\r\n\r\n<b>Step 6:</b>\r\n\r\nIdentify user needs\r\n\r\nGet at least 15 insights\r\n\r\n-each idea should be able to become a basis for a design project. Needs a way to be able\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What\'s this for?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>A UX Agency Perspective </strong>\r\n\r\nby Mike Davison, Community TA &amp; UX Project Manager\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNeedfinding is probably the most important and UX Designer\'s arsenal.\r\n\r\nNeedfinding is a very powerful way to generate ideas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Submit</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An explanation of the design brief you chose and how it relates to the activity you observed.</li>\r\n	<li>Thorough descriptions of your observations for each of the three people observed.</li>\r\n	<li>Photos or sketches of a design breakdown or opportunity for each of the three people observed. Remember: Each photo must have a caption that fully conveys the breakdown or opportunity.</li>\r\n	<li>A list of insightful user needs inspired by what you observed (at least 15). If you brainstormed with others, please include their names in your submission to recognize their contribution.</li>\r\n</ul>','HCI A1: Needfinding','','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2014-07-11 06:05:10','2014-07-11 06:05:10','',199,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=202',0,'revision','',0),
	(203,1,'2014-07-13 08:16:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong>Human-Computer InteractionÂ </strong>\n\n<em>by Scott Klemmer (Stanford)</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHuman - using the system\n\nComputer - machine/network of machines that runs the system\n\nInteraction - interface that represents the system and the user\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHCI\n\n- Design\n\n- Implementation\n\n- Evaluation\n\n<strong>Good Design</strong>\n\n- Gives people chores\n\n<strong>Good user interface</strong>\n\n- trememdous impact on both individuals ability to accomplish things &amp; societies\n\n<strong>Graphical User Interfaces</strong>\n\n- help put computing a hundred of desk enabling us to do things like create documents &amp; share photos, connect and find, &amp; the likes.\n\n<strong>Bad Design Costs</strong>\n\n- lives\n\n- money\n\n- time\n\n<strong>Design for people</strong>\n\n- tasks, goals &amp; values drive development\n\n- work w/ users throughout the development/process\n\n- Access decisions from the advantage point of users, their work and their environment\n\n- pay attention to peoples abilities and situation\n\n- talk to actual experts\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>To learn more</strong>\n\n<b>-HCI Classes</b>\n\n-Don Norman, The Design of Everyday things\n\n- Annual ACM CHI conference\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>The power of prototyping</strong>\n\n- prototyping grounds communication\n<ul>\n	<li>feedback</li>\n	<li>collab</li>\n	<li>hypothesis</li>\n	<li>reflective conversation</li>\n	<li>trying things</li>\n	<li>learning through exploration</li>\n	<li>insights</li>\n</ul>\nPrototyping is a strategy for efficiently dealing w/ things that are hard to predict\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPrototyping helps you:\n<ul>\n	<li>Get feedback quickly</li>\n	<li>Fewer options</li>\n	<li>Focus on goals</li>\n	<li>Evolve designs</li>\n</ul>\n|----------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------|\n\nBeginning Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â Time Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Find\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBeginning\n<ul>\n	<li>Broad possibilities</li>\n	<li>Narrow in</li>\n	<li>Altenatives</li>\n</ul>\nTime\n<ul>\n	<li>Narrow in</li>\n	<li>Alternating focus &amp; flair</li>\n</ul>\nEnd\n<ul>\n	<li>small issues</li>\n	<li>fonts</li>\n	<li>colors</li>\n	<li>layouts</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Beginning</strong>\n\n- What kind of app mobile/desktop service?\n\n<strong>Palm-pilot</strong>\n\n- one of first PDAs (Personal Digital Assistant)\n\nSource: \"The philosophy of the handheld\" Wired magazine, Oct 1999\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>The rights of a prototype</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>should not be required to complete</li>\n	<li>should be easy to change</li>\n	<li>gets to retire</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Evaluating Designs Motivation and menu</strong>\n\nHow to measure success?\n<ul>\n	<li>personal preference</li>\n	<li>Whatever feels like</li>\n	<li>open ended</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Why evaluate design w/ different types of people</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>hard to predict</li>\n	<li>different knowledge</li>\n	<li>hard to predict what people would actually do</li>\n	<li>to know if people can figure out how to use it</li>\n	<li>do they swear, giggle when using it</li>\n	<li>compare to other design</li>\n	<li>how design change users behavior</li>\n	<li>what new practices might encourage</li>\n	<li>things change over time</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Different methods achieve different goals</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Usability studies</strong>\n\n- Common and straight forward way to find and fix interface bugs in existing software\n\n&lt;-----------------------------------------------------------------------&gt;\n\ninformal Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â formal\n\n<strong>Controlled experiments</strong>\n\n- cam limit the real world applicability when they are done in a contrived lab setting\n\n<strong>Ways of getting feedback</strong>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Survey:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>feedback from a large number of responses</li>\n	<li>automatically tally results</li>\n	<li>what they say theyd do and what they actually do</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Focused Groups:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>gather small group of people &amp; discuss a design or idea</li>\n	<li>tease out the colleagues things that they might not say on their own</li>\n	<li>make up answers</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Feedback from experts:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>Peer critique</li>\n	<li>Dogfeeding</li>\n	<li>heurtistic evaluation</li>\n	<li>structured format</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Comparative experiments:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>two or more experiment and comparing its performance</li>\n	<li>w/c option is more important</li>\n	<li>much more actionable</li>\n	<li>actual behavior</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Participant observation:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>observing people do what they actually do in their actual environment</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Simulation and formal models:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>more formal way of studying HCI</li>\n	<li>with structures and modes</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Issues to consider:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>reliability precision</li>\n	<li>generalize-ability</li>\n	<li>realism</li>\n	<li>work involved</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>BIRTH OF HCI</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>July 1945</li>\n	<li>Vannevar Bush</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Memex</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Future interactive desk system memex</li>\n	<li>all of the worlds info will be available on desktops</li>\n	<li>wrote of how future technologies could argument human</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Grace Hopper</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>invented the first compiler</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>The Graphical User Interface</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>users input perform directly on top of systems output</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Output</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>input output</li>\n	<li>makes interface easy</li>\n	<li>to understand and intuitive</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Mouse and Hypertect</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Key foundation for the web</li>\n	<li>1945 - Dong Engelbart</li>\n	<li>invented the mouse</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;','HCI Notes week 1 - 2','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-07-13 08:16:01','2014-07-13 08:16:01','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=203',0,'post','',0),
	(206,1,'2014-07-14 13:08:14','2014-07-14 13:08:14','Task: Find 10 articles about the difference of UX and UI and summarize it\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttp://www.smashingmagazine.com/2010/10/05/what-is-user-experience-design-overview-tools-and-resources/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.helloerik.com/ux-is-not-ui\r\n\r\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_interface_design\r\n\r\nhttp://www.practicalecommerce.com/articles/3902-Understanding-User-Experience-vs-User-Interface\r\n\r\nhttp://www.quora.com/User-Experience/Whats-the-difference-between-UI-and-UX-design\r\n\r\nhttp://www.nngroup.com/articles/definition-user-experience/\r\n\r\nhttp://mashable.com/2009/01/09/user-experience-design/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.webdesignerdepot.com/2012/06/ui-vs-ux-whats-the-difference/\r\n\r\nhttp://designshack.net/articles/graphics/the-difference-between-ui-and-ux/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.linkedin.com/groups/What-is-Difference-Between-UI-2231152.S.187152376\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe main idea\r\n\r\n<strong>UX</strong>\r\n\r\n- The over all experience of the user on the website.(since we are talking about UX and UI in terms of web development)\r\n\r\n<strong>UI</strong>\r\n\r\n- The combination of the look and feel of the design and how the design works.','UX and UI','','publish','open','open','','ux-and-ui','','','2014-07-14 13:08:14','2014-07-14 13:08:14','',0,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=206',0,'post','',0),
	(207,1,'2014-07-14 13:08:14','2014-07-14 13:08:14','Task: Find 10 articles about the difference of UX and UI and summarize it\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttp://www.smashingmagazine.com/2010/10/05/what-is-user-experience-design-overview-tools-and-resources/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.helloerik.com/ux-is-not-ui\r\n\r\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_interface_design\r\n\r\nhttp://www.practicalecommerce.com/articles/3902-Understanding-User-Experience-vs-User-Interface\r\n\r\nhttp://www.quora.com/User-Experience/Whats-the-difference-between-UI-and-UX-design\r\n\r\nhttp://www.nngroup.com/articles/definition-user-experience/\r\n\r\nhttp://mashable.com/2009/01/09/user-experience-design/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.webdesignerdepot.com/2012/06/ui-vs-ux-whats-the-difference/\r\n\r\nhttp://designshack.net/articles/graphics/the-difference-between-ui-and-ux/\r\n\r\nhttp://www.linkedin.com/groups/What-is-Difference-Between-UI-2231152.S.187152376\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe main idea\r\n\r\n<strong>UX</strong>\r\n\r\n- The over all experience of the user on the website.(since we are talking about UX and UI in terms of web development)\r\n\r\n<strong>UI</strong>\r\n\r\n- The combination of the look and feel of the design and how the design works.','UX and UI','','inherit','open','open','','206-revision-v1','','','2014-07-14 13:08:14','2014-07-14 13:08:14','',206,'http://rachellesalvadora.com/?p=207',0,'revision','',0),
